<subSubSection id="A58A652EFFFBFFE4DFEFFD3BFE4F9078" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="279" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" type="description">
<paragraph id="ED2F36A5FFFBFFE1DFEFFD3BFB46957E" blockId="1.[174,1233,715,1094]" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">
E t y m o l o g y. Named after its 
<typeStatus id="322B8807FFFBFFE1DD50FD3BFD6494BE" box="[604,654,715,742]" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">type</typeStatus>
locality, 
<location id="E84F607EFFFBFFE1DDF1FD3BFC9B94BE" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:653987B3FFFBFFE4DFA2FDF5FE4F9078:E84F607EFFFBFFE1DDF1FD3BFC9B94BE" box="[765,881,715,742]" country="Iran" county="Tabriz. It" municipality="Forests" name="Qaradagh" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" stateProvince="Azarbayjan-e Sharqi">Qaradagh</location>
(Turkish: “black mountain”) 
<collectingMunicipality id="0D4BACDFFFFBFFE1DFA2FD1BFEE8955E" box="[174,258,747,774]" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">Forests</collectingMunicipality>
massive located in north of 
<collectingRegion id="2F54F847FFFBFFE1DD42FD1BFC9F955E" box="[590,885,747,774]" country="Iran" name="Azarbayjan-e Sharqi" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">East Azerbaijan province</collectingRegion>
in northwestern 
<collectingCountry id="95877635FFFBFFE1DB4CFD1BFB98955E" box="[1088,1138,747,774]" name="Iran" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">Iran</collectingCountry>
<quantity id="2A689B40FFFBFFE1DB74FD1BFB3B955E" box="[1144,1233,747,774]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.47" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" unit="km" value="147.0">147 km</quantity>
northwest of 
<collectingCounty id="044E4E29FFFBFFE1DE46FCFBFE5D957E" box="[330,439,779,806]" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">Tabriz. It</collectingCounty>
has the richest flora in 
<collectingCountry id="95877635FFFBFFE1DDC4FCFBFD10957E" box="[712,762,779,806]" name="Iran" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">Iran</collectingCountry>
with about 775 known plant species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED2F36A5FFFBFFE1DFEFFCDBFB4C921E" blockId="1.[174,1233,715,1094]" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">
D i a g n o s i s. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2A904D26FFFBFFE1DDBCFCDCFCD3951D" box="[688,825,812,838]" class="Insecta" family="Psilidae" genus="Chyliza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exenuata">
<emphasis id="DFE4EAB7FFFBFFE1DDBCFCDCFCD3951D" box="[688,825,812,838]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">C. exenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having arista thickened in basal third with dense black hairs and lacking anteroventral comb of black spinules in male fore tibia; hind femur with black subapical spot (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFFBFFE1DD63FC9BFD4695DE" box="[623,684,875,902]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,852,874]" captionTargetBox="[241,1143,176,830]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[232,1200,147,837]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 6–8. Chyliza qaradaghi, sp. n., holotype ♀: 6 — left wing, 7 — pattern of hind leg, 8 — antenna, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453154" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453154/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">fig. 7</figureCitation>
). New species is characterized by the following combination of characters: head yellow (except occiput); antennal postpedicel 2 times longer than high at base; hind tibia having large lateral black area on 2/3 apical half; surstyli with straight lateral margin (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFFBFFE1DEB1FC3BFDE295BE" box="[445,520,971,998]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[170,203,1735,1757]" captionTargetBox="[347,1015,968,1716]" captionTargetId="figure-8@3.[342,1065,963,1732]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 9–11. Chyliza qaradaghi, sp. n., genitalia: 9 — ovipositor, lateral view, 10 — hypopigium, dorsal view, 11 — aedeagus. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453156/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">fig. 10</figureCitation>
), apical lobes of aedeagus rhombic, triangular to top (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFFBFFE1DB74FC3BFB2895BE" box="[1144,1218,971,998]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[170,203,1735,1757]" captionTargetBox="[347,1015,968,1716]" captionTargetId="figure-8@3.[342,1065,963,1732]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 9–11. Chyliza qaradaghi, sp. n., genitalia: 9 — ovipositor, lateral view, 10 — hypopigium, dorsal view, 11 — aedeagus. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453156/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">fig. 11</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="2A904D26FFFBFFE1DFDEFC1CFEB7925D" box="[210,349,1004,1030]" class="Insecta" family="Psilidae" genus="Chyliza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exenuata">
<emphasis id="DFE4EAB7FFFBFFE1DFDEFC1CFEB7925D" box="[210,349,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">C. exenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
head completely black (except antennae); antennal postpedicel more than 2 times longer than high at base; hind tibia entirely yellow (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFFBFFE1DC33FBFBFC6D927E" box="[831,903,1035,1062]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,896,918]" captionTargetBox="[259,1061,199,868]" captionTargetId="figure-345@4.[243,1113,174,895]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 12–15. Chyliza extenuata, ♀: 12 — total view, left; 13 — head, lateral view; 14 — hypopigium, dorsal view; 15 — aedeagus. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453158" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453158/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">fig. 12</figureCitation>
); surstyli with concave lateral margin (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFFBFFE1DE03FBDBFEB2921E" box="[271,344,1067,1094]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,896,918]" captionTargetBox="[259,1061,199,868]" captionTargetId="figure-345@4.[243,1113,174,895]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 12–15. Chyliza extenuata, ♀: 12 — total view, left; 13 — head, lateral view; 14 — hypopigium, dorsal view; 15 — aedeagus. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453158" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453158/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">fig. 14</figureCitation>
), apical lobes of aedeagus rectangular with chopping straight apex (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFFBFFE1DB5CFBDBFB73921E" box="[1104,1177,1067,1094]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,896,918]" captionTargetBox="[259,1061,199,868]" captionTargetId="figure-345@4.[243,1113,174,895]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 12–15. Chyliza extenuata, ♀: 12 — total view, left; 13 — head, lateral view; 14 — hypopigium, dorsal view; 15 — aedeagus. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453158" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453158/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">fig. 15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED2F36A5FFFBFFE1DFA2FBABFE8B922E" blockId="1.[174,353,1115,1142]" box="[174,353,1115,1142]" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">D e s c r i p t i o n</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED2F36A5FFFBFFE4DFEFFB7BFB40920F" blockId="1.[174,1233,1163,1286]" lastBlockId="4.[166,1225,1052,1463]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="279" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">
F e m a l e. Body length: 
<quantity id="2A689B40FFFBFFE1DD08FB7BFDA492FE" box="[516,590,1163,1190]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
, wing length: 
<quantity id="2A689B40FFFBFFE1DDF0FB7BFCB192FE" box="[764,859,1163,1190]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
, wing width: 
<quantity id="2A689B40FFFBFFE1DB0FFB7BFB8892FE" box="[1027,1122,1163,1190]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.4 mm</quantity>
, antenna length: 
<quantity id="2A689B40FFFBFFE1DE09FB5BFE88929E" box="[261,354,1195,1222]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
. General coloration of body shiny black covered with mainly white tomentous hairs and yellow legs. H e a d: Antenna mainly yellow; scapus red-brownish; pedicel shiny red-brownish dorsally and yellow ventrally, with shiny yellow setules; postpedicel about 2 times longer than high, narrowed apically, with slightly concave dorsal margin; arista basidorsal, thickened in basal third with dense black hairs. Ratio of postpedicel length to its width to stylus length — 2/1/4. Frons yellow, weakly pollinose, 
<emphasis id="DFE4EAB7FFF8FFE2DCB3FAEDFB6E936F" box="[959,1156,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="277">frontorbital plate</emphasis>
in the upper portion of the frons with triangular black patch, its acute angle reaches the middle of frons; ocellar triangle black, reaches anterior margin of frons. Face red-brownish, weakly white pollinose. Cheeks under an eyes with a weak brownish spot. Occiput black and postgena yellow. Lower postocular setules pale yellow. Eyes finely haired, high of eyes 1.6 times longer than wide. mouthparts darkish, with white setulae; palpi black. With one pair of divergent postocellar setae, one pair of convergent inner vertical setae, one pair of outer vertical setae, two pairs of orbital setae. Length: height: width ratio — 1.5/2/1 (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFF8FFE2DB53FA0DFB579040" box="[1119,1213,1533,1560]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[173,206,1104,1126]" captionTargetBox="[223,1152,174,1092]" captionTargetId="figure-315@2.[229,1155,603,1103]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2–5. Chyliza qaradaghi sp. n., head: 2, 3 — female (2 — lateral view, 3 — dorsal view), 4, 5 — male (4 — lateral view, 5 — dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453152" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453152/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="277">fig. 2, 3</figureCitation>
). T h o r a x: Black, with pale yellow and white pubescent; one pair of dorsocentral, one pair of acrostichal, one pair of supralar, one pairs of postalar, 3 pairs of scutellar bristles. L e g s: Mainly yellow, with fine light hairs; fore and mid legs yellow; hind leg yellow, femur with latero-dorsal black subapical spot, tibia latero-ventrally blackish in apical 2/3, hind basitarsus about equal in length to rest tarsomeres combined (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFF8FFE2DC36F96DFC9390E0" box="[826,889,1693,1720]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,852,874]" captionTargetBox="[241,1143,176,830]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[232,1200,147,837]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 6–8. Chyliza qaradaghi, sp. n., holotype ♀: 6 — left wing, 7 — pattern of hind leg, 8 — antenna, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453154" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453154/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="277">fig. 7</figureCitation>
). W i n g s: Evenly brownish; veins brown. Lower calypter bare (except margin, with yellow cilia). Halter mainly yellow, black in basal (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFF8FFE2DE5BF92DFE7F90A0" box="[343,405,1757,1784]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,852,874]" captionTargetBox="[241,1143,176,830]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[232,1200,147,837]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 6–8. Chyliza qaradaghi, sp. n., holotype ♀: 6 — left wing, 7 — pattern of hind leg, 8 — antenna, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453154" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453154/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="277">fig. 6</figureCitation>
). A b d o m e n: Length: 
<quantity id="2A689B40FFF8FFE2DDA6F92DFCEC90A0" box="[682,774,1757,1784]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="277" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
, blackish and shiny, mainly with black and white tomentous. Genitalia: Length of ovipositor (segments 8 to 10 and cerci) 
<quantity id="2A689B40FFF8FFE2DB8EF90DFB229140" box="[1154,1224,1789,1816]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="277" unit="m" value="0.8">0.8 m</quantity>
. Epiproct and cerci fused, length 0.25. Sternite 8 with one distinct apical setae. Epiproct and hypoproct with some short setae and 4 pairs of long hairs, length of apical pair (
<quantity id="2A689B40FFFEFFE4DB58FBECFB2A926F" box="[1108,1216,1052,1079]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" unit="mm" value="0.17">0.17 mm</quantity>
) two times longer than supapical pairs. Segment 8 without any setulae on surface (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFFEFFE4DB52FBCCFB76920F" box="[1118,1180,1084,1111]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[170,203,1735,1757]" captionTargetBox="[347,1015,968,1716]" captionTargetId="figure-8@3.[342,1065,963,1732]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 9–11. Chyliza qaradaghi, sp. n., genitalia: 9 — ovipositor, lateral view, 10 — hypopigium, dorsal view, 11 — aedeagus. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453156/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">fig. 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
