, antenna length: 
<quantity id="2A689B40FFFEFFE4DFAAFB8CFEE992CF" box="[166,259,1148,1175]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
. H e a d: Length of ocellar triangle about 2 times longer than wide. Ocellar triangle black short, length relatively equal as wide. Cheeks under an eyes with a distinct brownish spot. Occiput mostly black. High of eyes 1.48 times longer than wide (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFFEFFE4DB12FB4CFB91928F" box="[1054,1147,1212,1239]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[173,206,1104,1126]" captionTargetBox="[223,1152,174,1092]" captionTargetId="figure-315@2.[229,1155,603,1103]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2–5. Chyliza qaradaghi sp. n., head: 2, 3 — female (2 — lateral view, 3 — dorsal view), 4, 5 — male (4 — lateral view, 5 — dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453152" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453152/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">fig. 2, 3</figureCitation>
). Fore tibiae without anteroventral comb of black spinules. Genitalia: Surstyli well developed, with straight lateral margin, apical lobes of aedeagus rhombic, triangular to apex (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFFEFFE4DB4DFB0CFB51934F" box="[1089,1211,1276,1303]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[170,203,1735,1757]" captionTargetBox="[347,1015,968,1716]" captionTargetId="figure-8@3.[342,1065,963,1732]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 9–11. Chyliza qaradaghi, sp. n., genitalia: 9 — ovipositor, lateral view, 10 — hypopigium, dorsal view, 11 — aedeagus. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453156/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">fig. 10, 11</figureCitation>
). Other characters as in female.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED2F36A5FFFEFFE4DFD7FACCFDEB930F" blockId="4.[166,1225,1052,1463]" box="[219,513,1340,1367]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">H o s t p l a n t unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED2F36A5FFFEFFE4DFD7FAACFB6193EF" blockId="4.[166,1225,1052,1463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">
E t y m o l o g y. Named after its 
<typeStatus id="322B8807FFFEFFE4DD56FAACFD61932F" box="[602,651,1372,1399]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">type</typeStatus>
locality, 
<location id="E84F607EFFFEFFE4DDF7FAACFC87932F" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:653987B3FFFBFFE4DFA2FDF5FE4F9078:E84F607EFFFEFFE4DDF7FAACFC87932F" box="[763,877,1372,1399]" country="Iran" county="Tabriz. It" municipality="Forests" name="Qaradagh" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" stateProvince="Azarbayjan-e Sharqi">Qaradagh</location>
(Turkish: “black mountain”) 
<collectingMunicipality id="0D4BACDFFFFEFFE4DFAAFA8CFF1393CF" box="[166,249,1404,1431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Forests</collectingMunicipality>
massive located in north of 
<collectingRegion id="2F54F847FFFEFFE4DD44FA8CFC8693CF" box="[584,876,1404,1431]" country="Iran" name="Azarbayjan-e Sharqi" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">
East 
<collectingCountry id="95877635FFFEFFE4DD8DFA8CFD1493CF" box="[641,766,1404,1431]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
province
</collectingRegion>
in northwestern 
<collectingCountry id="95877635FFFEFFE4DB3BFA8CFB8293CF" box="[1079,1128,1404,1431]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Iran</collectingCountry>
<quantity id="2A689B40FFFEFFE4DB7CFA8CFB2393CF" box="[1136,1225,1404,1431]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.47" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" unit="km" value="147.0">
<locationDeviation id="FC9D2F87FFFEFFE4DB7CFA8CFB2393CF" box="[1136,1225,1404,1431]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.47" pageId="4" pageNumber="279" unit="km" value="147.0">147 km</locationDeviation>
</quantity>
northwest of 
<collectingCounty id="044E4E29FFFEFFE4DE32FA6CFE4393EF" box="[318,425,1436,1463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Tabriz. It</collectingCounty>
has the richest flora in 
<collectingCountry id="95877635FFFEFFE4DDBFFA6CFD0E93EF" box="[691,740,1436,1463]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Iran</collectingCountry>
with about 775 known plant species.
</paragraph>
